works.description:
I have been the owner of Fab Find Foodie 

since 1/1/2010.  I own the domain, and the accounts on Twitter, Facebook, 

Pinterest, Technorati, and StumbleUpon, to name a few.  I came across a  
picture of my original blog design button on Google this afternoon which  
took me to another blog.  After researching the code, it shows clearly
that  
the author of Fab Foodie copied my button design and saved it as her own. 
 
She whitd out the word Find and tried unsuccessfully to add brown hair on 

top of the blonde in the design.  (You can still see the blonde showing  
through the edges.)  I paid a designer to design my website, and have all 

of our corresponding emails as proof saved.  In addition, I have contacted
 
her, since she is the designer and let her know someone unlawfully used
her  
design that I paid her to create for me.  I have links to the coding on
the  
mentioned bloggers website showing the button information was MINE, which 

mean is was taken without permission and pawned off as her own.  I have  
worked with over 100 companies nationwide as Fab Find Foodie.  I have also
 
competed in cooking competitions as Fab Find Foodie.  From what I saw, her
 
blog was created in 2011, mine was 2010.
